* Birthright = My mother once wore this, but it is now mine
  This was your mother's ring, and she wielded it like a blade. Grim, dangerous men bent when its seal pressed wax. You remember the smell of hot resin and sea-salt in her hair, the way she would turn the signet once before a bargain, as if testing the world's grain for weakness. She said the ring would secure the family's future, and you mean to see that through.
